Encouraging
Waſh your hands, put on your night-gown. Take courage—I tell you, Banquor is buried, all but the blood that was ſhed at his diſpatching;
Fear. and that has no likeneſs to be known by. Are you afraid he'll come out of his grave again? To bed, to bed, to bed. There is a knocking at the gate. Come, come, come. What is done cannot be undone. To bed, to bed, to bed.

